title: 19th Annual Barking Spider Bash XC
description: Barking Spider XC--desert classic race course! choose from 9-27miles of off road fun. Kid race free after main event, ages 9 under. Raffles and post race refreshments available!
course: Spider race features a fun, easy, 9 mile lap course with rolling terrain and terrific spectator viewing. The course includes the imfamous "Skateboard Park" descent, a twisting, turning tunnel of thrills. There is a new climbing section near the end of the course, so you might want to inspect? Same course as last year, we'll pre-mark lightly 1week prior to event date. thanks and enjoy!!!
notes: START TIMES: CAT 3 Beginners (1 lap) and Trailblazers (1/4 lap) - 11:40 pm CAT 2 Sports (2 laps) - 11:35pm CAT 1 Experts (3 laps) - 11:30pm Pros (3 laps) - 11:29pm Kids under 9 race (free) - 2:15pm.
directions: Here are detailed directions to the Spider: Take 2nd Nampa exit (whether coming from east or west) Go south over freeway to Garriety, turn right go under railroad tracks, then turn left, and then right on 12th Avenue South. Follow SIGNS toward Murphy & Melba out past hospital, 15 miles after leaving Nampa the road will drop down to the Snake River, where you will cross over the bridge BEARING to the left at the "Y" towards Murphy 3/4 of a mile after crossing river, turn right on Reynolds Creek Road - go 1.5 miles (keep driving thru stinky Dairy Farm) and event is on the right-hand-side at the Hemingway ORV area.

title: 2015 Ronde Van Ketchum
description: A road tour of almost all of the hills around Ketchum:  Warm Springs area, north of Ketchum to the top of Phantom Hill, Trail Creek road including the White Clouds both ways and the end of the pavement of Trail Creek, and almost every hill in Elkhart.
registration:
$20 cash at durance or the Perch.  you must fill out an athlete release and bring $20 cash only for registration.
No online registration. 
Registration is available until 1800 on June 19th.
notes: This is a tour, not a race.  Pace is moderate.
directions:
Start is at durance, N43.679254 W114.36464.
There is a GPX file available for the route:  Look on the online race flyer at http://www.durance.com/map_Ronde.html

title: St. Lukes Sports Medicine Idaho State Criterium C
Tamarack Resort Bike Endurbro
description: 6 stage enduro ride. Family friendly and at your own pace. We are using lift access at Tamarack Resort. Bike specific trails with awesome flow. Runs are 5-15min long.
course: Nothing really extreme  as far as the trail riding. Everything can be ridden on a trail or XC bike. 6in bikes usually have the most fun of all!
registration:
Early Registration thru July 1 st----Licensed adults $40, non-licensed $50,  Junior = $20 Onsite Registration July 18-19 Licensed adults $50, non-licensed $60 Junior = $20
$20 Lift tickets are seperate, cash or check please.
notes: This is probably the only chance to ride Tamarack lifts this summer. Dont miss out on a unique opportunity utilizing quality trails.
directions: To get to Tamarack from Boise, Id. Head North on HWY55 to Donnelly, take a left on Roseberry rd. Follow the signs South til you find the resort on your right hand side of the road.

title: Coeur d' Alene Twilight Criterium
description: Downtown Twilight criterium. @ 3/4 mile, 5 lefts and 1 right turn w a 3 block finishing straight.
course: @ 3/4 mile, 5 lefts and 1 right turn w a 3 block finishing straight.
registration: on site Registration from 3:30 pm up until 30 min before the start of each race. online at https://www.eventbrite.com/e/2015-cda-downtown-crit-fest-tickets-18234420643
directions: The races start and end at Sherman Ave between 6th St and 7th St

title: CrosstoberFest 4
description: CrosstoberFest IV is a two day Cyclocross race that is part of the Wildest CX Series. Crosstoberfest benefits families living on the autism spectrum in Bonner County.
course: Saturday and Sunday races are at the same facility but different courses. Saturday will be fast and open. Sunday more technical. We are fortunate to have a permanent course and each year we work to make it better.
registration: You may register online or day of race. Online registrants receive a beer mug.
directions: From the south take 95 North. Exit at the first Sandpoint exit just after crossing the Long Bridge. Follow road to First Street. Take First Street to Cedar Street and continue to follow the road to the left. At second light go right US 2. Take a left at the next light (Larch Street), Go to the round about and take a right on Boyer (North). Go about 1 mile north to the University of Idaho Extension on the right (after the second set of railroad tracks. Address is 2504 North Boyer in Sandpoint.
